-- Bulgari, Lufthansa, Fiat, Iberia, Intesa, L'Oreal: Europe Equity Preview
-- Jeff Kearns
-- 2010-04-22T04:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-04-21/bulgari-fiat-iberia-intesa-l-oreal-mobistar-sa-europe-equity-preview.html

          
          
             The following companies’ shares may
have unusual moves in European trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  
 Bulgari SpA (BUL IM): The world’s third-largest jeweler was
raised to “overweight” from “equal weight” at Morgan
Stanley, which increased its target price to 7.50 euros.  
 Deutsche Lufthansa AG (LHA GY): The airline plans to run a
full flight schedule, allowing it to resume receiving deliveries
of jet fuel.  
 Fiat SpA (F IM): The country’s biggest carmaker said it
plans to separate its agricultural and truckmaking units from
carmaking and aims to double revenue at the auto division by
2014.  
 Iberia Lineas Aereas de Espana SA (IBLA SM): American
Airlines parent AMR Corp. said it received “tentative”
approval from the U.S. Department of Transportation for its
planned trans-Atlantic alliance with British Airways Plc and
Iberia, Spain’s largest airline.  
 Intesa Sanpaolo SpA (ISP IM) and UniCredit SpA (UCG IM):
Italy’s Antitrust Authority said the country’s lenders acted
like an “oligopoly” in setting service costs.  
 L’Oreal (OR FP): The world’s largest cosmetics maker agreed
to buy Essie Cosmetics to expand in the nail color and care
market in the U.S. It didn’t give financial terms.  
 Mobistar SA (MOBB BB): Belgium’s second-biggest mobile-
phone operator may report first-quarter profit excluding some
items of 60.3 million euros, the average of six analyst
estimates compiled by Bloomberg.  
